summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2005 JEEP LIBERTY. WHILE TURNING INTO A DRIVEWAY AT APPROXIMATELY 2 MPH, THE REAR CONTROL ARM FRACTURED IN TWO WITHOUT WARNING. THE DEALER WAS CONTACTED (OVERLAND PARK DODGE/JEEP) AND STATED THAT THERE WAS NO RECALL. THE MANUFACTURER WAS MADE AWARE OF THE FAILURE AND STATED THAT THERE WAS NO RECALL. THE VEHICLE WAS NOT REPAIRED. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 130,000.
